(window.webpackJsonp=window.webpackJsonp||[]).push([[104],{vS7H:function(e){e.exports=[{id:1,type:"  template_dir",properties:[{name:"",description:"<p>The following arguments are supported:</p>",elementType:"p"},{name:"source_dir",description:'<li><p><a name="source_dir"></a><a href="#source_dir"><code>source_dir</code></a> - <strong>(Required)</strong> Path to the directory where the files to template reside.</p>\n</li>',elementType:"li",listDepth:1},{name:"destination_dir",description:'<li><p><a name="destination_dir"></a><a href="#destination_dir"><code>destination_dir</code></a> - <strong>(Required)</strong> Path to the directory where the templated files will be written.</p>\n</li>',elementType:"li",listDepth:1},{name:"vars",description:'<li><p><a name="vars"></a><a href="#vars"><code>vars</code></a> - <strong>(Optional)</strong> Variables for interpolation within the template. Note\nthat variables must all be primitives. Direct references to lists or maps\nwill cause a validation error.</p>\n</li>',elementType:"li",listDepth:1},{name:"",description:"<p>Any required parent directories of <code>destination_dir</code> will be created\nautomatically, and any pre-existing file or directory at that location will\nbe deleted before template rendering begins.</p>",elementType:"p"},{name:"",description:"<p>After rendering, this resource remembers the content of both the source and\ndestination directories in the Terraform state, and will plan to recreate the\noutput directory if any changes are detected during the plan phase.</p>",elementType:"p"},{name:"",description:"<p>Note that it is <em>not</em> safe to use the <code>file</code> interpolation function to read\nfiles created by this resource, since that function can be evaluated before the\ndestination directory has been created or updated. It <em>is</em> safe to use the\ngenerated files with resources that directly take filenames as arguments,\nas long as the path is constructed using the <code>destination_dir</code> attribute\nto create a dependency relationship with the <code>template_dir</code> resource.</p>",elementType:"p"},{name:"template-syntax",description:'<h2 id="template-syntax">\n<a class="anchor" href="#template-syntax" name="template-syntax">\xbb</a>\n  Template Syntax\n</h2>',elementType:"h2"},{name:"",description:'<p>The <code>template</code> argument is processed as\n<a href="/docs/configuration/expressions.html#string-templates">Terraform template syntax</a>.</p>',elementType:"p"},{name:"",description:"<p>However, this provider has its own copy of the template engine embedded in it,\nseparate from Terraform itself, and so which features are available are decided\nbased on what Terraform version the provider was compiled against, and not\non which Terraform version you are running.</p>",elementType:"p"},{name:"",description:"<p>To include values from your configuration in rendered templates, pass them\nvia the <code>vars</code> argument as shown below:</p>",elementType:"p"},{name:"",description:'<div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight hcl"><code><span class="n">resource</span> <span class="s2">"template_dir"</span> <span class="s2">"init"</span> <span class="p">{</span>\n  <span class="c1"># ...</span>\n\n  <span class="n">vars</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">{</span>\n    <span class="n">foo</span>  <span class="o">=</span> <span class="s2">"${var.foo}"</span>\n    <span class="kp">attr</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="s2">"${aws_instance.foo.private_ip}"</span>\n  <span class="p">}</span>\n<span class="p">}</span>\n</code></pre></div>',elementType:"div"},{name:"attributes",description:'<h2 id="attributes">\n<a class="anchor" href="#attributes" name="attributes">\xbb</a>\n  Attributes\n</h2>',elementType:"h2"},{name:"",description:"<p>This resource exports the following attributes:</p>",elementType:"p"},{name:"destination_dir",description:"The destination directory given in configuration.\nInterpolate this attribute into other resource configurations to create\na dependency to ensure that the destination directory is populated before\nanother resource attempts to read it.\n",elementType:"li",listDepth:1}],docsUrl:"https://www.terraform.io/docs/providers/template/r/dir.html",docType:""}]}}]);